- "Average population" is the mean population of the locations where cases were reported, grouped by ethnicity;
- The query ranks ethnicities by the total number of cases in descending order to identify the ethnicity with the highest number of cases.

- "Total cases" refer to the sum of all reported COVID-19 cases for each location;
- "Average cases" for race and ethnicity are calculated by averaging the number of cases for each demographic group within the same location;
- "Location" refers to geographical areas such as cities, counties, or states.

sql:
SELECT AVG(total_cases_per_location) AS average_total_cases_across_locations
FROM (
  SELECT SUM(cases) AS total_cases_per_location
  FROM demographic_data
  GROUP BY location_id
);

